20/03/2005
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- President Ibrahim Rugova announced on Friday (18 March) that he has nominated Bajram Kosumi to succeed Ramush Haradinaj as prime minister of Kosovo.
The president made the decision after meeting representatives from the main political parties in the province.
Kosumi, 45, the incumbent environment minister, is deputy leader of the Alliance for the Future of Kosovo, the party led by Haradinaj.
The Kosovo Parliament is due to hold a debate on the nomination next week.
(Danas - 19/03/05;
AFP, KosovaLive, Tanjug - 18/03/05)
